==English==

===Etymology===
A calque of Chinese {{zh-tsp|丟臉|丢脸|diū liǎn}}, literally meaning “lose face”.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|head=to [[lose]] [[face]]|loses face|losing face|lost face}}

# {{idiom}} To lose the respect of others, to be humiliated or experience public disgrace.

